land. It was reinforced by the vogue for Germanic names in Victorian times."]},{"name":"Friederich","meanings":["from <i>frid</i> ‘peace’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power’; a royal and imperial name from an early date."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Friedrich Von Truhendingen IVCount of Truhendigen was born in 1189, in Austria, his father, Friedrich III von Truhendingen Edelfreier  Graf von Truhendingen, was 22 and his mother, Eufemia Von Hirscher, was 23. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Agnes Von Ortenburg. He died in 1253, in his hometown, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1189–1253":"1189–1253","1198–Female":"1198–Surnud","1199–1245":"1199–1245","1222–1294":"1222–1294","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1168–1198":"1168–1198","1166–1229":"1166–1229","1245":"1245","1168":"1168","1189":"1189","1222":"1222","1166":"1166","1199":"1199","1198":"1198","1253":"1253","1294":"1294","1229":"1229","Chemnitz, Sachsen, Deutschland":"Chemnitz, Sachsen, Saksamaa","Truhendingen, Austria":"Austria","Austria":"Austria"},"fi":{"1189–1253":"1189–1253","1198–Female":"1198–Kuollut","1199–1245":"1199–1245","1222–1294":"1222–1294","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1168–1198":"1168–1198","1166–1229":"1166–1229","1245":"1245","1168":"1168","1189":"1189","1222":"1222","1166":"1166","1199":"1199","1198":"1198","1253":"1253","1294":"1294","1229":"1229","Chemnitz, Sachsen, Deutschland":"Chemnitz, Sachsen, Saksa","Truhendingen, Austria":"Itävalta","Austria":"Itävalta"},"fr":{"1189–1253":"1189–1253","1198–Female":"1198–Décédée","1199–1245":"1199–1245","1222–1294":"1222–1294","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1168–1198":"1168–1198","1166–1229":"1166–1229","1245":"1245","1168":"1168","1189":"1189","1222":"1222","1166":"1166","1199":"1199","1198":"1198","1253":"1253","1294":"1294","1229":"1229","Chemnitz, Sachsen, Deutschland":"Chemnitz, Sachsen, Allemagne","Truhendingen, Austria":"Autriche","Austria":"Autriche","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Friedrich Von Truhendingen IVCount of Truhendigen est né en 1189,